# Overview

The Erlware mode for [Emacs](http://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/) and
[XEmacs](http://xemacs.org) mode is an updated version of the standard
Erlang mode found on
[erlang.org](http://www.erlang.org/doc/man/erlang_mode.html).

Enhancements to the original mode include:

  * [edoc](http://www.erlang.org/doc/man/edoc.html) formatting
    for the skeleton code templates.

  * Skeleton code reformatting for consistency.

Planned improvements to the mode include menu and hot-key support for running 
[Sinan]({relocatable: ../sinan/index.page}) and
[Faxien]({relocatable: ../faxien/index.page}) commands.

Much of the [documentation](http://www.erlang.org/doc/man/erlang_mode.html)
for the original mode still applies to the erlware mode.
